  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Some functions in the deposit contract are marked `@public` when they have no reason to be (other than implementation details of the vyper stack, i.e. they are easier to test when marked `@public`).\r\n\r\nI suggest in the spirit of keeping this contract as simple and small as possible, we reduce the size of the public API by remove the `@public` decorators where we can.\r\n\r\nAt the moment that is:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n@public\r\n@constant\r\ndef to_little_endian_64(value: uint256) -> bytes[8]:\r\n```\r\n\r\nassuming we also address #34.",
